Davidson urges us to rethink the usual opposition to liberation and to gay and lesbian visibility within queer studies as well as standard definitions of celebrity. The conventional ban on openly discussing the homosexuality of public figures meant that media reporting at the time did not focus on his protagonists' private lives. At the same time, the careers of these "semi-visible" gay celebrities should be understood as a crucial halfway point between the era of the open secret and the present-day post-liberation era in which queer people, celebrities very much included, are enjoined to come out.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aCelebritiesxSexual behaviorzUnited StatesxHistory. 0aFamexSocial aspectszUnited StatesxHistory. 0aGay authorszUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aGay liberation movementzUnited StatesxHistory. 0aSexual minoritieszUnited StatesxIdentityxHistory. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / American / General.2bisacsh  aCelebrity.  aGore Vidal.  aJames Baldwin.  aSusan Sontag.  agay and lesbian liberation.  aqueer theory.  asexual liberation.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2020 Englishz978311070474708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2020z9783110704532oZDB-23-DKU08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311069228040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150360920440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503609204423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781503609204.jpg  a978-3-11-069228-0  SUP Complete eB